Wesley Tuttle (born December 30, 1917, in Lamar, Colorado; died September 29, 2003) was an American country music singer.
He married actress Marilyn Myers in 1947 and acted with her in several Western films, in addition to recording the duet "Never" with her.
Eyesight problems forced Tuttle into retirement in the 1970s.
Wesley's last recording was in 1997, when he sang a verse of Detour on The Old Cowhands CD, "A Tribute to Wesley Tuttle".
